@email = auth.{{$guid}}@example.com
@password = Passw0rd123

### Register — creates a User + Organization (Organization starts PENDING)
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Rest",
  "lastName": "Client",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "organizationName": "Rest Client Org"
}

### Current session (cookie set by register/login above)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/me

### Active sessions for this user
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/sessions

### [dev/test only] fetch the verification token instead of scraping server stdout
# @name verificationToken
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/test/verification-token?email={{email}}

### Verify email — flips the org PENDING -> TRIALING (see tenant.http for the tenant-side effects)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "{{verificationToken.response.body.$.data.token}}"
}

### Refresh — rotates the refresh token, issues a new access token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/refresh

### Login again in a fresh "session" (only one org on this account, so organizationSlug is optional)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Login with the wrong password — expect 401 UNAUTHORIZED
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword123"
}

### Logout — revokes the current session's refresh token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/logout
